Invalid bundle for a DSSE-content envelope logged to Rekor v1 with the
experimental hashedrekord-over-DSSE encoding (kind=hashedrekord/0.0.1).
The envelope signature does not verify under the bundle's certificate (it
was made with a different key entirely).

Construction:
  1. Sign in-toto statement A as DSSE with key/cert #1 → bundle1
     (happy-path source)
  2. Sign in-toto statement A as DSSE with an unrelated key/cert #2 →
     bundle2
  3. In bundle1, replace the envelope signature and the RFC3161 timestamps
     with those from bundle2.

Signed against production Sigstore Public Good using the
sigstore-conformance/extremely-dangerous-public-oidc-beacon workflow
identity. No custom trusted_root.json is shipped; the test uses the
default production trust root.
